                          Employee - Sorry it's too late.

                          Moral of the story.
                          <span class="white-space-pre">

                          <!-- -->
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <!-- -->
                          Leaders should listen to and take care of the talent before it's too late.
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <!-- -->
                          Because employees will go where they are valued and compensated.
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>
                          <!-- -->
                          <!-- -->
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <!-- -->
                          The best employees don't leave because they stop liking their job. They leave because they feel undervalued and underappreciated. Consistent pay stagnation signals a lack of growth and recognition.
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>
                          <!-- -->
                          <!-- -->
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <!-- -->
                          It's not just about the money; it's about respect and acknowledgment. A competitive salary is a sign that an employer values your contributions and wants to invest in your future.
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>
                          <!-- -->
                          <!-- -->
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <!-- -->
                          Retention starts with appreciation. Proactive leadership means listening, rewarding, and recognizing talent regularly. Don't wait until they're out the door to offer what they deserved all along.
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>
                          <!-- -->
                          <!-- -->
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <!-- -->
                          Invest in your people today, because the cost of losing top talent is far greater than you might think.
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>
                          <span>
                           <br/>
                          </span>
                          <span class="white-space-pre">
                          </span>

                  <div class="feed-shared-update-v2 feed-shared-update-v2--minimal-padding full-height relative feed-shared-update-v2--e2e artdeco-card" data-urn="urn:li:activity:7206335343627755521" id="ember92" role="region">

                    <div class="display-flex flex-column flex-grow-1">
                     <h2 class="visually-hidden">
                      Feed post number 2
                     </h2>
                     <div id="fie-impression-container">
                      <!-- -->
                      <div class="relative">
                       <div class="update-components-actor display-flex update-components-actor--with-control-menu">
                        <!-- -->

                             2h

                      <div class="feed-shared-update-v2__description-wrapper mr2" style="" tabindex="-1">
                       <div class="feed-shared-inline-show-more-text feed-shared-update-v2__description feed-shared-inline-show-more-text--minimal-padding feed-shared-inline-show-more-text--3-lines" tabindex="-1">
                        <div class="update-components-text relative update-components-update-v2__commentary" dir="ltr">
                         <!-- -->
                         <span class="break-words tvm-parent-container">
                          <!-- -->
                          <span dir="ltr">
                           <!-- -->
                           My post may offend someone, but I feel compelled to show a mirror to those who especially
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           <a class="app-aware-link" data-test-app-aware-link="" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ACoAACcBrvYB27_hn-myajQm17mjLar5CLTPa10" target="_self">
                            <span>
                             <a class="ember-view" href="/in/samira-iftikhar/" id="ember255">
                              <!-- -->
                              Samira Iftikhar
                              <!-- -->
                             </a>
                            </span>
                           </a>
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           ,
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           <a class="app-aware-link" data-test-app-aware-link="" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ACoAABlp9DMBoWVqUgTP2lVvmVI9oi0L6jJAT8E" target="_self">
                            <span>
                             <a class="ember-view" href="/in/rabia-pervaiz-3ab960ba/" id="ember256">
                              <!-- -->
                              Rabia Pervaiz
                              <!-- -->
                             </a>
                            </span>
                           </a>
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           at
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           <a class="app-aware-link" data-test-app-aware-link="" href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/ninesol-technologies/" target="_self">
                            <span>
                             <span>
                              <!-- -->
                              Ninesol Technologies
                              <!-- -->
                             </span>
                            </span>
                           </a>
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           <!-- -->
                           <!-- -->
                           <a class="app-aware-link" data-test-app-aware-link="" href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/ninesol-technologies1/" target="_self">
                            <span>
                             <span>
                              <!-- -->
                              NineSol Technologies
                              <!-- -->
                             </span>
                            </span>
                           </a>
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           consider themselves as untouchable in this world, forgetting that there is a higher power above them.
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <!-- -->
                           It's often said that what goes around comes around. We've seen managers who misuse their power, mistreat employees, and act solely for their own benefit. Despite raising these concerns with higher-ups, our voices were ignored. I don't know how many girls and boys have lost their future, honor, and livelihood because of their actions. Now, the tables have turned, and those who caused so much harm are facing the consequences.
                           <!-- -->
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <!-- -->
                           This is a reminder to everyone: leadership is about uplifting others, not tearing them down. The corporate world has its way of balancing the scales.
                           <!-- -->
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           <!-- -->
                           <!-- -->
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <!-- -->
                           Note: I commend the organization for taking a positive step in this direction and hope to see more actions like this in the future.
                           <!-- -->
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>

                      <!-- -->
                      <!-- -->
                      <!-- -->
                      <div class="feed-shared-update-v2__description-wrapper mr2" style="" tabindex="-1">
                       <div class="feed-shared-inline-show-more-text feed-shared-update-v2__description feed-shared-inline-show-more-text--minimal-padding feed-shared-inline-show-more-text--3-lines" tabindex="-1">
                        <div class="update-components-text relative update-components-update-v2__commentary" dir="ltr">
                         <!-- -->
                         <span class="break-words tvm-parent-container">
                          <!-- -->
                          <span dir="ltr">
                           <!-- -->
                           A pioneering strategy has been developed to digitalize the transport system in Rawalpindi, marking a first in Pakistan. The Punjab Information Technology Board (PITB) will create the software for this digital public transport system, which will include a control room and an e-tag system at the Pirwadhai Bus Terminal.
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <!-- -->
                           This system will gather comprehensive data on vehicles at the terminal, such as registration numbers, owner's details, fitness certificates, and route information. It aims to enhance road and passenger safety by ensuring only vehicles that meet safety standards are allowed to operate.
                           <!-- -->
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <!-- -->
                           The digitized transport system, modeled after those in Paris, London, and the United States, will serve as a blueprint for future projects across Punjab. Once completed, the project will not only improve travel comfort and vehicle fitness levels but also allow citizens to file online complaints against public and government transport services.
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <!-- -->
                           Rashid Ali, Secretary of the Regional Transport Authority (RTA), described the project as a "masterpiece," with IT facilities provided by the Punjab Government's IT sector. Senior officials are set to visit Rawalpindi on September 2 to finalize the plans.
                           <!-- -->
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <span>
                            <br/>
                           </span>
                           <a class="app-aware-link" data-test-app-aware-link="" href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/?keywords=it&amp;highlightedUpdateUrns=urn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7236236478643658752">
                            <span class="visually-hidden">
                             hashtag
                            </span>
                            <span>
                             <span aria-hidden="true">
                              #
                             </span>

                            </span>
                           </a>
                           <span class="white-space-pre">
                           </span>
                           <!-- -->
                           <!-- -->
                           <a class="app-aware-link" data-test-app-aware-link="" href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/?keywords=rta&amp;highlightedUpdateUrns=urn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7236236478643658752">
                            <span class="visually-hidden">

                            </span>
